  "prompt": "I've postnatal depression, Dr said the recovery's good & can return to work.my boss tells me the workload and pressure will be heavy.should I return?",
  "response": "This is a delicate situation that requires careful consideration of your mental health. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Prioritize your health:\n- Your mental well-being should come first\n- Discuss your concerns with your doctor and therapist\n- Ensure you're truly ready for work stress\n\n2. Workplace options:\n- Request a phased return with reduced hours\n- Ask for a lighter workload initially\n- Discuss potential flexible working arrangements\n- Seek support from HR about accommodations\n\n3. Legal protections:\n- Many countries have laws protecting employees with mental health conditions\n- You might be entitled to reasonable workplace adjustments\n\n4. Additional support:\n- Consider counseling or support groups\n- Maintain open communication with your healthcare providers\n- Talk to trusted family/friends about your concerns\n\n5. Self-care strategies:\n- Develop stress management techniques\n- Ensure you have support systems in place\n- Monitor your mental health closely\n\nRecommendation: Consult with your doctor and have a detailed discussion with your boss about your return, focusing on a supportive, gradual transition that protects your mental health.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further or explore specific strategies?",
